Returns the number of elements the binary heap can hold without reallocating.

# Examples

Basic usage:

```
use std::collections::BinaryHeap;
let mut heap = BinaryHeap::with_capacity(100);
assert!(heap.capacity() >= 100);
heap.push(4);
```
